}$ subshell with two half-filled\n$m_j=\\pm\\frac{1}{2}$ orbitals forming a narrow gap by hybridization, then\ndriven to a conducting state by configuration mixing (spin-charge\nfluctuations). UTe$_2$ displays similarities to UPt$_3$ with its $5f$ dominated\nFermi surfaces rather than a strongly localized Kondo lattice system.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sun, 21 Mar 2021 14:25:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-03-23"}
